A technical property generally refers to a characteristic or attribute that defines or describes the technical aspects of an object, system, material, or process. These properties are usually measurable or quantifiable and are critical in determining how something will function or perform in a specific context.
The torque required to move the air damper, which is a mechanical device that controls the amount of air entering into a duct, chimney, vent, or airwork tool.
The amount of torque required to keep the air damper in a fixed position
The surface area of the air damper, measured in square meters (m²).
The angular rotation of the air damper is the measure of the rotation angle of the damper blade in degrees.

The time taken by the air damper to move from one position to another

Positioning signal of an air damper is a control signal that determines the position of the damper blade in an HVAC system.
The degree of protection of the air damper defines its resistance to intrusion from foreign bodies and water.

The temperature range of the medium in which the air damper operates
The level of humidity in the surrounding environment required for the proper operation of the air damper
